  "texts": [
    "This can reduce the difficulty of network optimization and improve network performance.",
    "In some cases, features are even transferred across scales, feeding features from the encoder into different scales of the decoder.",
    "In this paper, inspired by NAFNet [2], we furthermore introduce a simple gating mechanism into cross-scale feature fusion increasing the nonlinearity of fusion.",
    "Based on the gating mechanism, we can extract the features needed by different scale decoders which improves the correction effect of the network.",
    "Specifically, as shown in Fig. 3, our Multi-Scale Gating Module (MCGM) up-samples or down-samples the features at different scales according to the required shape of the module output, then concatenates them at the channel dimension and adjusts the number of channels using 1×1 convolution."
